cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.AI 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents a probabilistic topic model. It could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with discovering topical themes in collections of documents. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it deals with organizing unstructured collections of documents. It may also be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as topic models are often used in social network analysis. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it presents a model that combines the advantages of two existing models to improve topic modeling.
